[1] Costa Rica
Date: Thu, 23 Jun 2005 10:00! :50 -0500
From: Dr. Alfonso J. Rodriguez <ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: Mi punto.com Noticias, 21 Jun 2005 [translated by Jorge
Gonzales Mendoza, edited]
<http://www.mipunto.com/punto_noticias/noticia_medicina.jsp?tipo=MEDICINA&archivo=050621153810.jt15jev1.txt>


Dengue fever cases increased 72 percent in Costa Rica
---------------------------------------------------
Dengue fever cases increased 72 percent in Costa Rica during the
first 5 months of 2005 compared to 2004, and this has worried health
authorities.

5220 cases of dengue fever had been reported up to 11 Jun 2005,
compared to 3031 cases for the same time period in 2004, according to
the Ministry of Health.

"These figures are alarming", said Dr. Francisco Cubillo,
Vice-Minister for Health. He recalled that the rainy season is yet to
come, and this is the time when there is active reproduction of the
_Aedes aegypti_ mosquito, reported the newspaper La Nacion.

Dengue causes fever, chills, sweat, cough, and diarrhea, as well as
respiratory distress. There is a hemorrhagic form of dengue fever,
which occurs when a patient is infected for a 2nd time, and it may
even lead to death.

--
Alfonso J. Rodriguez, M.D.
<ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>

