[2] Yemen
Date: Thu, 23 Jun 2005 12:16:54 -0400 (EDT)
From: A-Lan Banks <A-Lan.Banks@thomson.com>
Source: Khaleej Times, Dubai, 23 June 2005 [edited]
<http://www.khaleejtimes.com/DisplayArticle.asp?xfile=data/middleeast/2005/June/middleeast_June666.xml?ion=middleeast&col=>


Dengue kills 30 in southern Yemen; nearly 1500 infected
---------------------------------------------------
An outbreak of the mosquito-borne dengue fever has killed at least 30
people in southern Yemen over the past 4 weeks, a health ministry
official said on Thursday.

"We have received reports of 30 deaths and 1487 infected cases," the
official told DPA on condition of anonymity.

The official said infections were reported in the southern provinces
of Shabwa, Aden, Abyan, Dalaa, Hadhramout and Houdieda [also spelled
Hodeida].

He said the worst infected area was the Red Sea province of Houdieda,
about 230 kilometres southwest of the capital Sanaa, where the
disease has so far infected nearly 400 people, of whom 15 died.

