[3] Philippines (Iloilo)
Date: Fri, 24 Jun 2005 15:15:04 -0400 (EDT)
From: Dr. Alfonso J. Rodriguez <ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: Sun Star, Philippines, 25 Jun 2005 [edited]
<http://www.sunstar.com.ph/static/ilo/2005/06/25/news/dengue.fever.cases.in.city.drop.html>


Dengue fever cases in city drop
-------------------------------------------
Cases of dengue fever in Iloilo City dropped to only 13 in the 1st
half of 2005, from 80 cases during the same period in 2004. "These
are reported and confirmed by hospitals in the city," City Health
Officer Urminico Baronda said of the 13 cases.

The reported cases are distributed, based on the City Health Office
statistics, [as follows:] City Proper and Arevalo have 4 cases each;
Molo 2; and Mandurriao, La Paz, and Jaro, one each.

Though the cases decreased this year, it is no reason to be
complacent, Baronda said. "Dengue cases have lessened this year but
we should not be relaxed. Mosquitoes that bring dengue fever
recognize no one," he warned.

Baronda advised Ilonggos to always keep their surroundings clean to
avoid the deadly mosquitoes.

He also suggested coordination between barangay officials and
residents in the campaign against dengue fever.

--
Alfonso Rodriguez, M.D.
<ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>

